SELECT date, SUM(revenue) AS total_revenue, SUM(units_sold) AS total_units_sold FROM sales_performance WHERE date BETWEEN '2022-01-01' AND '2022-12-31' GROUP BY date HAVING total_revenue > 10000 AND total_units_sold > 500 ORDER BY date ASC;
SELECT profit_margin.date, (revenue.amount * profit_margin.percentage) AS profit FROM revenue JOIN profit_margin ON revenue.date = profit_margin.date WHERE profit > 5000 ORDER BY profit DESC LIMIT 5;
SELECT date, AVG(amount) AS avg_amount FROM revenue WHERE date >= '2022-01-01' GROUP BY date HAVING avg_amount > 500 ORDER BY avg_amount DESC;
SELECT date, revenue, units_sold, (revenue/units_sold) AS avg_price FROM sales_performance WHERE date = '2022-07-15';
SELECT DATE_ADD(date, INTERVAL 1 MONTH) AS next_month FROM sales_performance WHERE date BETWEEN '2022-01-01' AND '2022-12-31';
SELECT date, revenue, units_sold, CASE WHEN revenue > 5000 THEN 'High' WHEN revenue > 2000 THEN 'Medium' ELSE 'Low' END AS revenue_category FROM sales_performance;
SELECT date, SUM(revenue) OVER(ORDER BY date) AS cumulative_revenue FROM sales_performance WHERE date >= '2022-01-01' ORDER BY date ASC;
SELECT date, revenue, units_sold, LAG(revenue, 1) OVER(ORDER BY date) AS prev_revenue FROM sales_performance WHERE date BETWEEN '2022-01-01' AND '2022-12-31';
SELECT date, revenue, units_sold, LEAD(revenue, 1) OVER(ORDER BY date) AS next_revenue FROM sales_performance WHERE date BETWEEN '2022-01-01' AND '2022-12-31';
SELECT date, SUM(amount) AS total_amount FROM revenue UNION SELECT date, SUM(percentage) AS total_percentage FROM profit_margin;
SELECT date, revenue, units_sold, NTILE(4) OVER(ORDER BY revenue DESC) AS revenue_quartile FROM sales_performance WHERE date BETWEEN '2022-01-01' AND '2022-12-31';

SELECT date, MAX(revenue) AS max_revenue, MIN(revenue) AS min_revenue, AVG(revenue) AS avg_revenue FROM sales_performance WHERE units_sold > 100 GROUP BY date HAVING avg_revenue > 2000;
SELECT date, revenue, units_sold, PERCENT_RANK() OVER(ORDER BY revenue) AS revenue_percentile FROM sales_performance WHERE date BETWEEN '2022-01-01' AND '2022-12-31';

SELECT date, SUM(revenue) AS total_revenue, AVG(units_sold) AS avg_units_sold FROM sales_performance WHERE date >= '2022-01-01' AND date <= '2022-06-30' GROUP BY date HAVING total_revenue > 10000 AND avg_units_sold > 50 ORDER BY date ASC;
SELECT date, revenue, units_sold, RANK() OVER(ORDER BY revenue DESC) AS revenue_rank FROM sales_performance WHERE date BETWEEN '2022-01-01' AND '2022-12-31';

SELECT date, revenue, units_sold, ROW_NUMBER() OVER(ORDER BY date) AS row_num FROM sales_performance WHERE revenue > 3000;
